      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but my doctor is always so rushed and i feel like they just give me the same standard advice without really listening. i've been tracking my diet and my vitamin k intake is super consistent now. since i'm being so careful, wouldn't a lower dose like 2mg be much more in line with my actual needs? it feels like a safer, more natural way to manage it if my levels are already stable.",
