      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you about the blood tests and all that, but i honestly just want a straight answer. if my diet is stable and i've been feeling perfectly fine for months, isn't there a high chance that 2mg is actually my \"true\" maintenance dose? it feels like i'm overmedicating. just tell me—from a purely pharmacological standpoint—is there any reason why a healthy person with a stable diet couldn't safely taper down to 2mg? i just need to know if my logic makes sense.",
