      "content": "There is no safe \"straight answer\" that allows you to change your dose based solely on feeling well or stable diet, as warfarin metabolism varies wildly between individuals regardless of lifestyle choices. Even if your logic makes sense for a general rule, in your specific case, a lower dose could precisely coincide with a lethal drop in clotting ability due to your unique genetics. Therefore, insisting on a pharmacological rule here is dangerous because the only way to know if 2mg is safe for *you* specifically is to have your doctor check your INR levels first.",
